body:
I'm seeing what seems like a regression bug. The following code (unless I'm missing something obvious) should not throw an exception:

```
using (SKPaint p = new SKPaint()) {
    p.IsStroke = false;
    if (p.IsStroke != false) {
        throw new Exception();
    }
}
```

But with SkiaSharp 1.53, I am seeing the exception thrown. When I downgrade to 1.49.1, the bug goes away (no exception thrown). This is on Win7 SP1 with VS 2015 Community Update 2, .NET framework 4.5.2.
